{
  "text": "Our experiments span 11 pairs of cooperative kernels and inputs, Responsiveness. Figure 5 reports, on three configurations, the average gather and execution times for the non-cooperative kernel with respect to the quantity of workgroups allocated to it. A logarithmic scale is used for time since gather times tend to be much smaller than execution times. The horizontal grey lines indicates the desired period for non-cooperative kernels. These graphs show a representative sample of our results; the full set of graphs for all configurations is provided in the extended version of this paper [CITATION_1] .",
